'''Raphael Dias Belloli''' ({{IPA|pt|ʁɐˈfiɲɐ}}; born 14 December 1996), known mononymously as '''Raphinha''', is a Brazilian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder|winger]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Spanish football updater|Barcelona}} club [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]]. Known for his pace, playmaking, work rate, and finishing, he is considered one of the best players in the world.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Swan |first1=Rob |last2=Malyan |first2=Christy |last3=Murray |first3=Will |date=10 November 2023 |title=The 25 best footballers in the world right now - ranked in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-football-players-in-the-world/ |access-date=15 May 2025 |website=GiveMeSport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=4 June 2025 |title=2025 FC 100: Salah among best wingers in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45179056/2025-fc-100-salah-best-wingers-mens-soccer |access-date=4 June 2025 |website=ESPN}}</ref>

Raphinha began his career with Brazilian club [[Avaí FC|Avaí]], before signing for the Portuguese [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]] in 2016, where he made his professional debut. In 2018, he joined fellow [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Sporting CP]], winning the [[Double (association football)|double]] of the [[Taça de Portugal]] and [[Taça da Liga]] in 2019.

After having played for [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]] and [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]], Raphinha signed for Spanish club [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in 2022 for a transfer worth €58 million (£50 million). Despite initially struggling, in [[2024–25 FC Barcelona season|2024–25]], Raphinha had his breakthrough season, being integral to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] winning a [[domestic treble]] of the [[La Liga]] title, the [[Copa del Rey]], and the [[Supercopa de España]], while also finishing as the [[List of UEFA Champions League top scorers#Top scorers by season|Champions League's top scorer]].

After never being capped at youth level, Raphinha made his senior international debut in 2021, and was part of Brazil's squads at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], [[2024 Copa América]] and [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]].

==Early life==
Raphinha was born in [[Porto Alegre]], Brazil where he grew up in [[Restinga, Porto Alegre|Restinga]], a [[favela]] far from the city centre.<ref name="12Things">{{cite web |title=12 Things You Don't Know About Me By Raphinha |url=https://www.theplayerstribune.com/posts/raphinha-leeds-united-premier-league-soccer |website=The Players' Tribune |date=26 August 2021 |publisher=Minute Media |access-date=2 September 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=12 Histórias que Você Não Sabe Sobre Mim por Raphinha |url=https://www.theplayerstribune.com/br/posts/carta-raphinha-leeds-12-historias-sobre-mim-que-voce-nao-sabe |website=The Players' Tribune |date=26 August 2021 |publisher=Minute Media |access-date=2 September 2021}}</ref><ref name="yep" /> His father is of [[Italian Brazilians|Italian]] descent and his mother is [[mixed-race Brazilian]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/colunas/rafael-reis/2021/03/18/italia-deve-convocar-toloi-para-eliminatorias-e-ja-mira-outros-brasileiros.htm|title=Reportagem: Rafael Reis – Itália deve convocar Tolói para eliminatórias e já mira outros brasileiros|website=www.uol.com.br}}</ref> His father was a jobbing musician.<ref name="athletic">{{Cite web |last1=Hay |first1=Phil |last2=Lang |first2=Jack |date=26 November 2022 |title=Raphinha, the fiery Brazilian who has swapped the Champions League for Leeds |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/2121303/2020/10/13/raphinha-leeds-united-transfer/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=3 October 2021 |website=The Athletic }}</ref> He had a difficult upbringing where he describes sharing a bedroom with his parents, younger brother and pets; struggling to pay travel costs and at points having to beg for food.<ref name="12Things" />

At age seven, Raphinha attended [[Ronaldinho]]'s birthday party due to his father and uncle's relationship with the player and have since become friends.<ref name="12Things" />

Before starting his professional football career, Raphinha participated in the ''várzea'' tournaments until the age of 18,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gauchazh.clicrbs.com.br/esportes/copa-do-mundo/noticia/2021/10/de-cria-da-restinga-e-recusado-na-dupla-gre-nal-a-parceiro-de-neymar-na-selecao-a-historia-de-raphinha-ckvcgkuzf003l017f9h4k434r.html|title=De cria da Restinga e recusado na dupla Gre-Nal a parceiro de Neymar na Seleção: a história de Raphinha|trans-title=From Restinga's offspring and refused in the duo Gre-Nal to Neymar's partner in the national team: the story of Raphinha|website=GZH.com|date=11 January 2021|access-date=11 May 2022|language=portuguese}}</ref> which he describes as "a network of independent matches and tournaments organised by the local community" below academy level in which any prospective player is allowed to participate.<ref name="12Things"/> The matches in these tournaments are played under harsh conditions, including home fans harassing opponent team players near changing rooms before matches, gunshots, clay pitches with dust and sand, intense heat, posts instead of nets and shirtless teams due to the lack of shirts/jerseys.<ref name="12Things"/>

==Club career==
===Avaí===
After unsuccessful trials with [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] and [[Grêmio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|Grêmio]], Raphinha started his career playing youth football with [[Imbituba Futebol Clube|Imbituba]], where he was later scouted by [[Avaí FC|Avaí]].<ref name="athletic" /> At 18 years old, Raphinha started his career with Avaí's youth squad.

===Vitória de Guimarães===
[[File:FC Salzburg versus Vitória Guimarães (UEFA Euroleague 23. November 2017) 12.jpg|thumb|right|Raphinha (behind) playing for Vitória de Guimarães in 2017|271x271px]]
On 2 February 2016, Raphinha signed for Portuguese side [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]], having been scouted at the Copa São Paulo de Futebol Júnior by [[Deco]], who signed him to his agency, D20 Sports, and arranged his transfer to Vitória.<ref name="athletic" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/sc/futebol/noticia/2016/02/avai-vende-jovem-rapinha-para-o-vitoria-de-guimaraes-de-portugal.html|title=Avaí vende jovem Raphinha para o Vitória de Guimarães, de Portugal|trans-title=Avaí sells youngster Raphinha to Vitória de Guimarães, of Portugal|language=pt|work=Globo Esporte |date=2 February 2016|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref> He made his debut for the ''Vimaranenses'' on 13 March 2016 against [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Vitória Guimarães 0–1 Paços de Ferreira|url=https://www.foradejogo.net/match.php?match=201615400012605 |website=ForaDeJogo|access-date=4 January 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club against [[C.S. Marítimo|Marítimo]] on 20 August 2016.<ref name="auto">{{cite web |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/en/news/10-facts-about-raphinha|title=10 FACTS ABOUT RAPHINHA|publisher=Leeds United|date=5 October 2020 |access-date=7 October 2020}}</ref> He made his first appearance in the [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League]] on 14 September 2017 against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]].<ref name="auto"/> He won the Vitória Guimarães Breakthrough Player of the Year in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.terra.com.br/esportes/lance/atacante-brasileiro-conquista-premio-inedito-de-revelacao-em-portugal,eb161fbb2f7c6e97437f423e40463970l89r3wfl.html |title=Brasileiro conquista prêmio inédito de revelação em Portugal|trans-title=Brazilian wins unprecedented award for revelation in Portugal |publisher=Terra |language=pt|date=7 December 2017|access-date=7 October 2020}}</ref> He scored 18 goals during 43 games (in all competitions) during the [[2017–18 Primeira Liga]] season for Vitória de Guimarães.<ref name="yep">{{cite web|url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/who-raphinha-rennes-winger-profile-leeds-united-target-deadline-day-transfer-2992920|title=Who is Raphinha – Rennes winger in profile as Leeds United target deadline day transfer|work=Yorkshire Evening Post|date=5 October 2020|access-date=7 October 2020}}</ref>

===Sporting CP===
In May 2018, Raphinha transferred to Portuguese club [[Sporting CP]] until 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.publico.pt/2018/05/23/desporto/noticia/v-guimaraes-confirma-saida-de-raphinha-para-o-sporting-1831393 |title=Raphinha assina por cinco épocas pelo Sporting |website=Público |language=pt |date=23 May 2018 }}</ref> He made his debut on 12 August against [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]]. He scored his first goal for the club on 20 September 2018 against [[FK Qarabag|Qarabag]] in the 2–0 victory in the [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2025157--sporting-cp-vs-qarabag/|title=Sporting CP 2 FK Qarabag 0 |publisher=[[UEFA]]|date=20 September 2018|access-date=7 October 2020}}</ref> He struggled in finishing with only four goals and as many assists, in particular due to a muscle injury which hampered his progress, but was a part of the side that won the [[2018–19 Taça de Portugal|2018–19]] [[Taça da Liga]] and [[Taça de Portugal]], scoring a penalty in the penalty shootout victory against [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Penalties smile on Sporting again as Lions retain Taça da Liga crown|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/1045-penalties-give-sporting-the-taca-da-liga|access-date=7 October 2020|publisher=PortuGOAL.net|date=26 January 2019}}</ref><ref name="auto"/>

===Rennes===
Raphinha signed for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] in 2019, with a transfer fee around €21 million,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/raphinha-no-rennes-e-a-sexta-maior-transferencia-de-sempre-do-sporting |title=Raphinha no Rennes é a sexta maior transferência de sempre do Sporting |website=Desporto |language=pt |date=25 November 2022 }}</ref> the club's record signing.<ref name="auto"/> He scored and gained an assist in his final game for the club during the [[2020–21 Ligue 1]] fixture against [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] in a 2–2 draw on 4 October 2020.<ref>{{Cite news |date=5 October 2020 |title=Raphinha's Rennes swansong gave Leeds United an enticing showcase of his undoubted potential |work=Leeds Live |url=https://www.leeds-live.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/leeds-united-raphinha-scout-report-19050107|access-date=7 October 2020}}</ref> He scored eight goals and gained seven assists during his time at the club, where he helped Rennes to a third-place finish and qualify for the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League]] during the [[2019–20 Ligue 1]] season.<ref>{{Cite news |date=5 October 2020 |title=Leeds Utd transfer news: Raphinha signs from Rennes for £17m  |publisher=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54415316|access-date=7 October 2020}}</ref>

===Leeds United===
[[File:Raphinha.jpg|thumb|200x200px|Raphinha with [[Leeds United]] in 2021]]
On 5 October 2020, Raphinha joined [[Premier League]] club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] on a four-year contract for an undisclosed fee reported to be in the region of £17 million, or about €20 Million.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Rayner |first=Stuart |date=5 October 2020 |title=Raphinha completes deadline-day switch to Leeds United |work=The Yorkshire Post |url=https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/raphinha-completes-deadline-day-switch-leeds-united-2993769 |access-date=5 October 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=6 October 2020 |title=Leeds United sign winger Raphinha from Rennes for £17m |work=The Independent |url= https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/leeds-united-transfer-raphinha-latest-news-rennes-ps17m-b829133.html |access-date=6 October 2020}}</ref>

On 19 October 2020, Raphinha made his debut as a second-half substitute in a 1–0 loss to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ames |first=Nick |date=19 October 2020 |title=Leeds United 0–1 Wolves: Premier League – as it happened |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2020/oct/19/leeds-united-v-wolves-premier-league-live |access-date=28 November 2020 |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> His full debut was at home to [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 22 November 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hay |first=Phil |date=24 November 2020 |title=Raphinha, an astute £17m buy with the diligence and flair to satisfy Bielsa |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/2216006/2020/11/24/leeds-raphinha-arsenal-analysis/ |access-date=28 November 2020 |website=The Athletic}}</ref> On 28 November 2020, Raphinha scored his first Leeds goal in a 1–0 away win over [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Magowan |first=Alistair |date=28 November 2020 |title=Everton 0–1 Leeds United: Raphinha's first Leeds goal sinks Toffees |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55025785 |access-date=28 November 2020 |website=BBC Sport }}</ref> His winning goal secured Leeds' first ever Premier League win at [[Goodison Park]] and their first league win at Everton since 1990.<ref>{{Cite news |date=28 November 2020 |title=Raphinha's excellent late goal gave Leeds a deserved victory in a match of many chances at Goodison Park |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2020/nov/28/everton-v-leeds-premier-league-live|access-date=28 November 2020}}</ref> He finished the season with six goals, all from league fixtures.{{Citation needed|date=December 2022}}

Raphinha scored his first goal of the season on 21 August 2021, in Leeds' first home game, a low-struck 72nd-minute equaliser from just inside the penalty area, in a 2–2 result against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dawkes|first=Phil|date=21 August 2021 |title=Leeds United 2–2 Everton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58193422|access-date=3 September 2021 |website=BBC Sport }}</ref> which was nominated as one of the Premier League's Goals of the Month for August.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/2233845|date=2 September 2021 |title=Luke and Raphinha Nominated for Premier League Goal of the Month!|access-date=3 September 2021 |work=Leeds Ynited F.C.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/66356|date=2 September 2021 |title=Pick August's Budweiser Goal of the Month!|access-date=3 September 2021 |work=Premier League}}</ref>

Raphinha ended the season as Leeds' top goalscorer with 11 goals, including the first goal of the game in the 2–1 away win against [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] on the last day of the season, from the penalty spot after being fouled by the Brentford goalkeeper [[David Raya]], saving Leeds from relegation to the [[EFL Championship|Championship]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61453546 |title=Brentford 1–2 Leeds |first=Simon |last=Stone |website=BBC Sport |date=22 May 2022 |access-date=22 May 2022}}</ref>

Over the summer transfer window, [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] had an agreement in place with Leeds to sign him, with both clubs agreeing a fee worth of £55 million, despite [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and [[Tottenham Hotspur]]'s interest. However, Raphinha preferred a move to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], despite their financial struggles. This led to Raphinha flying to Barcelona to complete a deal, being left out of Leeds's squad for their pre-season tour to Australia in order to finalise a transfer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4170032/2022/06/28/chelsea-close-to-agreeing-fee-for-raphinha-as-they-edge-ahead-of-arsenal-in-race-for-leeds-forward/ |title=Chelsea close to agreeing fee for Raphinha as they edge ahead of Arsenal in race for Leeds forward |website=[[The Athletic]] |date=28 June 2022 |access-date=22 December 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4165972/2022/07/13/raphinha-leeds-and-barcelona-reach-55m-agreement-in-principle-for-brazil-winger/ |title=Raphinha: Leeds and Barcelona reach £55m agreement in principle for Brazil winger |website=[[The Athletic]] |date=13 July 2022 |access-date=22 December 2024 }}</ref>

===Barcelona===
On 15 July 2022, Raphinha signed for [[La Liga]] club Barcelona on a five-year contract for a reported initial fee of £50m, potentially rising to £55&nbsp;million in add-ons.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 July 2022 |title=Agreement in principle to sign Raphinha |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2676187/agreement-in-principle-to-sign-raphinha |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221114081030/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2676187/agreement-in-principle-to-sign-raphinha |archive-date=14 November 2022 |access-date=24 July 2022 |website= |publisher=[[FC Barcelona]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Pope |first=Adam |date=15 July 2022 |title=Raphinha: Barcelona sign attacker from Leeds United in deal worth up to £55m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62168557 |access-date=15 July 2022 |website= |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He was initially presented without a name or number on his shirt due to registration issues, with the club needing to sell players to register players and make new signings.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/barcelona-must-sell-raphinha-bankroll-summer-spending/bltc6bddf04f9c7a98b |title=Barcelona must sell Raphinha to bankroll summer spending |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |date=19 June 2023 |access-date=22 December 2024 }}</ref>

====2022–24: Adaptation to Spain and La Liga title====
On 13 August, Raphinha made his debut for the club in 0–0 draw against [[Rayo Vallecano]] in the league.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 August 2022 |title=Barcelona frustrated by Rayo Vallecano as Lewandowski & Raphinha's La Liga debuts spoiled |url=https://www.goal.com/en-in/news/barcelona-frustrated-rayo-vallecano-opening-night/bltcd5e7b01eea1ab09 |access-date=16 August 2022}}</ref> On 3 September, he scored his first goal for ''Blaugrana'' in a 3–0 victory over [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] at the [[Ramón Sánchez Pizjuán Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62783164 |title=Barca maintain unbeaten start with win at Sevilla |author=Shamoon Hafez |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 September 2022 |access-date=26 January 2023}}</ref> On 13 September, he made his continental debut for the club starting in the 2–0 loss to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/champions-league/2022-2023/bayern-munich-v-barcelona-follow-live_sto9142270/story.shtml |title=Bayern Munich 2-0 Barcelona: Lucas Hernandez and Leroy Sane goals enough to see off Barca in Champions League |website=Eurosport |date=14 September 2022 }}</ref> At the end of the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League group stage|group stage]], Barcelona finished third, which put them in the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League knockout phase|knockout round play-offs]] for the second consecutive season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/barcelona-back-europa-league-where-they-belong-right-now/bltb94f0b887e0b4ef3 |title=Barcelona back where they belong right now: the Europa League |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |date=26 October 2022 |access-date=15 November 2022 |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231085208/https://www.goal.com/en/news/barcelona-back-europa-league-where-they-belong-right-now/bltb94f0b887e0b4ef3 |url-status=live }}</ref> Signed to be a replacement for struggling [[Ousmane Dembélé]], both competed for a starting spot with manager [[Xavi Hernandez|Xavi]] insisting that he wanted to keep both players, hoping to breed competition between them for starting spots on a team that was short on wingers.<ref name="BarçaCareer">{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/barcelona-must-sell-raphinha-bankroll-summer-spending/bltc6bddf04f9c7a98b |title=Barcelona must sell Raphinha to bankroll summer spending |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |date=16 April 2024 |access-date=22 December 2024 }}</ref> Over the course of the season, Dembélé's resurgence in form limited his opportunities to impress at his preferred right-wing position.<ref name="BarçaCareer"/>

On 16 January 2023, Barcelona won the [[2023 Supercopa de España final]], following a 3–1 victory over rivals [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in ''[[El Clásico]]'', winning his first title with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3023483/first-trophy-of-the-xavi-era |title=First trophy of the Xavi era |work=FC Barcelona |date=15 January 2023 |access-date=5 March 2023 |archive-date=19 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230119013317/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3023483/first-trophy-of-the-xavi-era |url-status=live }}</ref> On 16 February, Raphinha assisted and scored in a 2–2 draw against [[Manchester United]] in a [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Knockout round play-offs|knockout round play-off]] in the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] at the [[Camp Nou]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Whitwell |first=Laurie |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4217363/2023/02/17/man-utd-barcelona-rashford/ |title=Manchester United and Barcelona are on upward arcs — this was a worthy chapter in their rivalry |date=7 January 2023 |access-date=14 January 2023 |website=[[The Athletic]] |url-access=subscription}}</ref> Barcelona was eliminated from the tournament after losing 2–1 at the away leg at [[Old Trafford]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/manchester-united-vs-barcelona/478970|title=Man Utd 2-1 Barcelona (Agg:4-3): Antony off the bench to win Europa League play-off on big night for Erik ten Hag|work=Sky Sports|date=23 February 2023|access-date=24 February 2023|last=Bate|first=Adam}}</ref> In the second half of the season, he was handed a chance to impress when Dembélé picked up a muscle injury, but was inconsistent over that period, leading Raphinha to be in and out of the starting XI.<ref name="BarçaCareer"/> On 14 May, he assisted [[Robert Lewandowski]]'s second goal, as Barcelona defeated [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] 4–2 in the [[Derbi Barceloní]], confirming them as La Liga champions.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Barcelona crowned La Liga champions after derby win |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65590309 |access-date=14 May 2023 |archive-date=14 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230514210105/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65590309 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Booth |first=Chuck |title=Barcelona clinch La Liga title over Real Madrid after bashing city rival Espanyol 4-2 |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/barcelona-clinch-la-liga-title-over-real-madrid-after-bashing-city-rival-espanyol-4-2/ |access-date=14 May 2023 |website=CBSSports.com |date=14 May 2023 |language=en |archive-date=14 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230514213602/https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/barcelona-clinch-la-liga-title-over-real-madrid-after-bashing-city-rival-espanyol-4-2/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

After missing part of the [[2023–24 FC Barcelona season|new season]], Raphinha struggled to meet the expectations of fans and Barcelona's management in La Liga, despite support from his manager Xavi. He eventually lost his spot in the starting XI to young prospect [[Lamine Yamal]], who had already scored during Raphinha's absence due to injury and at the end of the first part of the season, he had scored only three goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.itatiaia.com.br/editorias/barcelona/2023/09/30/barcelona-confirma-lesao-em-raphinha-que-deve-ficar-fora-dos-jogos-do-brasil|title=Barcelona confirma lesão em Raphinha, que deve ficar fora dos jogos do Brasil|language=pt-br|date=1 October 2023|publisher=Itatiaia|access-date=1 October 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Aguiar|first=Gustavo Viola de|url=https://www.gazetaesportiva.com/times/barcelona/raphinha-brilha-em-vitoria-do-barcelona-e-comenta-disputa-com-yamal/|title=Raphinha shines in Barcelona's victory and comments on competition with Yamal|date=24 February 2024|access-date=24 March 2024|website=Gazeta Esportiva|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/noticia/2024/03/24/al-hilal-de-jorge-jesus-planeja-oferecer-meio-bilhao-de-reais-por-raphinha.ghtml|title=Jorge Jesus' Al-Hilal plans to offer half a billion reais for Raphinha|date=24 March 2024|access-date=24 March 2024|website=ge|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Lance!|url=https://www.lance.com.br/futebol-internacional/alvo-de-criticas-raphinha-e-defendido-por-xavi-no-barcelona.html|title=Target of criticism, Raphinha is defended by Xavi at Barcelona - Lance!|date=2 February 2023|access-date=24 March 2024|website=Target of criticism, Raphinha is defended by Xavi at Barcelona - Lance!|language=pt-BR}}</ref>

Despite a disappointing overall season, Raphinha played a key role in Barcelona's [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|Champions League campaign]], being involved in two goals in their 3–1 win over [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]] on 12 March, in the home leg, knocking them out with a 4–2 aggregate score.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 March 2024 |title=Barcelona 3-1 Napoli (4-2 on agg.): Robert Lewandowski among goals as Xavi's side make Champions League quarter-finals |url=https://www.tntsports.co.uk/football/champions-league/2023-2024/fc-barcelona-v-napoli-uefa-champions-league-live_sto10058242/story.shtml?welcome=eurosport |access-date=15 March 2024 |website=Eurosport |language=en}}</ref> On 10 April 2024, he scored his first Champions League goal by netting a brace in a 3–2 away win against [[Ligue 1]] champions [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] at the [[Parc des Princes]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|quarter-final]] first leg,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68773222 |title=Paris Saint Germain 2–3 Barcelona |publisher=BBC Sport |date=10 April 2024 }}</ref> and awarded as the Player of the Match.<ref>{{Cite web |last=MUGU |date=11 April 2024 |title=Barcelona secures edge with a 3–2 win over PSG in Champions League quarter-final {{!}} Ansiklopedika |url=https://ansiklopedika.net/en/barcelona-secures-edge-with-a-3-2-win-over-psg-in-champions-league-quarter-final/ |access-date=11 April 2024 |language=en-US |archive-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250220021602/https://ansiklopedika.net/en/barcelona-secures-edge-with-a-3-2-win-over-psg-in-champions-league-quarter-final/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> In the return leg at home, despite scoring the opening goal, the Parisian team overturned the aggregate score with a 4–1 win, eliminating Barça.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Kylian Mbappe bags brace as PSG stun Barcelona to reach Champions League semis |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-champions-league/articles/kylian-mbappe-bags-brace-as-psg-stun-barcelona-to-reach-champions-league-semis-2024-04-16 |access-date=18 April 2024 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-us |archive-date=4 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240504181315/https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-champions-league/articles/kylian-mbappe-bags-brace-as-psg-stun-barcelona-to-reach-champions-league-semis-2024-04-16 |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2024–25: Breakthrough season and goalscoring achievements====
Despite recording 10 goals and 11 assists in 37 appearances in his previous season, Raphinha's future at the Spanish club was uncertain and with Xavi leaving the managerial role, he was linked with a move away from the club, in order for Barcelona to raise funds amid their financial difficulties.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/barcelona/artigo/_/id/13752502/barcelona-novo-tecnico-enxerga-raphinha-peca-vital-detalha-futuro-clube|title=Staying at Barcelona? Outlet reveals how the new coach sees Raphinha in the squad and details the Brazilian's future at the club|date=6 June 2024|access-date=25 June 2024|website=ESPN.com|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/futebol-espanhol/noticia/2024/05/24/xavi-se-manifesta-apos-demissao-do-barcelona-as-coisas-nao-sairam-como-queriamos.ghtml|title=Xavi comments on his dismissal from Barcelona: "Things didn't go as we wanted"|date=24 May 2024|access-date=25 June 2024|website=ge|language=pt-BR}}</ref> He was the recipient of a contract offer worth €90 million from [[Saudi Pro League]] side [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]], with Barcelona's sporting director Deco informing his agent to look for another team for him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/futebol-espanhol/noticia/2024/05/17/crise-financeira-abala-o-barcelona-e-gera-embate-entre-xavi-e-presidente.ghtml|title=Financial crisis shakes Barcelona and sparks clash between Xavi and the president|date=17 May 2024|access-date=25 June 2024|website=ge|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/futebol-espanhol/noticia/2024/06/24/com-raphinha-na-mira-do-al-hilal-barcelona-traca-r-524-milhoes-para-venda.ghtml|title=With Raphinha targeted by Al-Hilal, Barcelona sets R$524 million as asking price for his sale|date=24 June 2024|access-date=25 June 2024|website=ge|language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tntsports.com.br/melhorfuteboldomundo/Al-Hilal-mira-Raphinha-e-Barcelona-aceita-negociar-por-no-minimo-90-milhoes-de-euros-20240624-0013.html|title=Al-Hilal targets Raphinha, and Barcelona agrees to negotiate for a minimum of €90 million|work=TNT Sports }}</ref> However, [[Hansi Flick]], who replaced Xavi as the new manager, decided to keep him.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Juanmartí|first=Toni|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/flick-canticos-existe-equipo-107593511|title=Flick: 'Chants towards me? The team is all that matters'|date=31 August 2024|access-date=1 September 2024|website=Diario Sport|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Fernández|first=Judith|url=https://es.e-noticies.cat/futbol/raphinha-roto-deco-ya-lo-ha-comunicado-y-su-socio-debe-irse-otro-equipo|title=Raphinha devastated: Deco has already communicated it, and his partner must go to another team|date=10 August 2024|access-date=1 September 2024|website=[[E-Notícies]]|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cronicaglobal.elespanol.com/culemania/primer-equipo/20240831/hansi-flick-defensa-de-deco-mercado-fichajes/882411804_0.html|title=Hansi Flick defends Deco after the transfer market|date=31 August 2024|access-date=15 September 2024|website=Crónica Global|language=es}}</ref> Highlighting his importance to the team, Flick named him as one of the team's captains for the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4092240/new-first-team-captains-confirmed|title=New first team captains confirmed|access-date=21 December 2024|website=www.fcbarcelona.com|language=en}}</ref>

Flick began his tenure with a different tactical approach than his predecessor, he positioned Raphinha centrally, behind Robert Lewandowski and flanked by wingers, which saw his form improve dramatically. On 31 August 2024, he scored his first hat-trick for Barcelona in a 7–0 thrashing at home against [[Real Valladolid]] in a La Liga match.<ref>{{Cite web |title=FC Barcelona vs Real Valladolid CF – LALIGA EA SPORTS |url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2024-2025-laliga-ea-sports-fc-barcelona-real-valladolid-cf-4 |access-date=31 August 2024 |website=Página web oficial de LALIGA {{!}} LALIGA |language=en}}</ref> Later that year, on 23 October, he scored a hat-trick in the Champions League in a 4–1 home win against Bayern Munich in the group stage and was named Player of the Match.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ballús |first=Pol |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5868632/2024/10/24/raphinha-barcelona-bayern-hat-trick/ |title=Raphinha's Bayern hat-trick is proof of his newfound confidence and Barcelona transformation |work=The New York Times |date=24 October 2024 }}</ref> A few days later, on 26 October, he netted his first goal in ''El Clásico'' and provided an assist in a 4–0 away win over Real Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Corrigan |first1=Dermot |last2=Ballús |first2=Pol |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5866056/2024/10/26/real-madrid-0-barcelona-4-mbappe-flick-lewandowski/ |title=Real Madrid 0 Barcelona 4 – Mbappe's Clasico to forget as Flick's team stun European champions |work=The New York Times |date=26 October 2024 }}</ref> During the match at the [[Santiago Bernabeu Stadium|Santiago Bernabéu]], Raphinha and his Barcelona teammates Lamine Yamal and [[Ansu Fati]] were targeted with racial abuse by a group of home supporters.<ref>{{cite web |date= 26 October 2024 |title='No place for these criminals in our society!' - Vinicius Junior sends support to Lamine Yamal, Raphinha & Ansu Fati after seeing Barcelona trio targeted with racist insults in El Clasico win at Real Madrid|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/no-place-criminals-society-vinicius-junior-sends-support-lamine-yamal-raphinha-ansu-fati-barcelona-trio-targeted-racist-insults-el-clasico-real-madrid/blt051e17049c4c2523#cs5523e9e83afd302b |access-date=28 October 2024 |website=[[goal.com]]|language=en}}</ref>

On 12 January 2025, Raphinha was named Player of the Match,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/raphinha-mvp-de-la-final-de-la-supercopa-de-espana-2025 |title=Raphina, designado MVP de la final de la Supercopa de España 2025 |trans-title=Raphina, named MVP of the 2025 Spanish Super Cup final |work=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |format=PDF |date=12 January 2025 |access-date=12 January 2025 |language=es}}</ref> after scoring a brace and providing an assist in a 5–2 victory over Real Madrid in the [[2025 Supercopa de España final|Supercopa de España final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj91ljy0r0xt |title=Barcelona came from behind to beat Real Madrid in an incident-packed Spanish Super Cup final in Saudi Arabia |publisher=BBC Sport |date=12 January 2025 }}</ref> On 21 January, he was named player of the match once again, after leading Barcelona to a comeback victory against [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in the Champions League. He contributed a brace, including a decisive goal in injury time, to secure a 5–4 away win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2025/1/21/controversial-raphinha-winner-seals-nine-goal-thriller-for-barca-in-benfica |title=Controversial Raphinha winner seals nine-goal thriller for Barca at Benfica |publisher=Al Jazeera |date= 21 January 2025 }}</ref> On 5 March, in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16]], Raphinha scored the only goal of an away win over Benfica, whilst being one man down<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/benfica-vs-fc-barcelona-score-highlights-hansi-flicks-side-win-first-leg-despite-pau-cubarsis-red-card/|title=Benfica vs. FC Barcelona score, highlights: Hansi Flick's side win first leg despite Pau Cubarsi's red card|date=5 March 2025|website=CBSSports.com}}</ref> and scored two goals and provided an assist on 11 March in the second leg of a 3–1 home win, securing a 4–1 aggregate victory and qualify to the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|quarter-finals]] of the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c1w08y0wpwjt| title=Yamal and Raphinha star as Barca breeze into last eight |date=12 March 2025}}</ref> On 9 April, he equaled [[Lionel Messi]]'s record of 19 goal involvements in a single Champions League season, set in the [[2011–12 UEFA Champions League|2011–12 season]], after scoring and assisting twice in a 4–0 win over [[Borussia Dortmund]] in the first leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#quarter-finals|Champions League quarter-finals]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Staff |first=G. M. S. |date=2025-04-10 |title=Ballon d'Or favourite Raphinha equals incredible Lionel Messi record for Barcelona |url=https://www.givemesport.com/thread/ballon-dor-favourite-raphinha-equals-incredible-lionel-messi-record-for-barcelona/ |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Barcelona 4-0 Dortmund (Apr 9, 2025) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/733610 |access-date=2025-04-13 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On 19 April, Rapninha scored two goals in Barcelona's 4–3 La Liga victory over [[Celta Vigo]], the latter of which marked his 50th goal for Barcelona.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title= Hotshot Raphinha reaches 50 goals |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4251650/hotshot-raphinha-reaches-50-goals |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=FC Barcelona}}</ref> On 30 April, in the first leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#semi-finals|semi-finals]], he surpassed Messi's record with 20 goal contributions, after assisting in the 3–3 draw against [[Inter Milan]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=1 May 2025|title=Raphinha Leaves Messi Behind and Sets His Sights on Cristiano in the Champions League|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-champions-league/articles-video/raphinha-leaves-messi-behind-and-sets-his-sights-on-cristiano-in-the-champions-league-2025-05-01|access-date=1 May 2025|website=beinsports.com}}</ref> In the second leg, on 6 May, despite scoring his side's third goal, after being two goals down, Inter Milan came back and Barcelona lost the match 4–3, being eliminated in the semi-finals of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bandini |first=Nicky |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/may/07/acerbi-goal-crazy-inter-warriors-champions-league |title=Acerbi's preposterous goal summed up 'crazy Inter's' last-chance warriors |work=The Guardian |date=7 May 2025 }}</ref> 

Raphinha finished his Champions League campaign as joint top scorer with 13 goals, alongside [[Serhou Guirassy]], and also led the tournament in assists with nine.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://de.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0291-1be52628e744-a25f57a62887-1000--champions-league-top-scorers-raphinha-joins-serhou-guiras/ |title=Champions League top scorers: Raphinha joins Serhou Guirassy out in front |publisher=UEFA |date=7 May 2025 }}</ref> On 11 May, he scored two goals against Real Madrid as Barcelona went on to win 4–3.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kallas |first=Fernando |date=May 11, 2025 |title=Barcelona edge closer to title with thrilling 4-3 win over Real Madrid |url=https://reuters.com/sports/soccer/barcelona-edge-closer-title-with-thrilling-4-3-win-over-real-madrid-2025-05-11 |url-status=bot: unknown |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250512084442/https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/barcelona-edge-closer-title-with-thrilling-4-3-win-over-real-madrid-2025-05-11/ |archive-date=12 May 2025 |access-date=May 15, 2025 |website=Reuters }}</ref> On 22 May, Raphinha extended his contract with Barcelona until 30 June 2028.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-22 |title=Agreement to renew Raphinha's contract to 2028 |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4271553/agreement-to-renew-raphinhas-contract-to-2028 |access-date=2025-05-22 |website= |publisher=FC Barcelona |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2025–26: Third league title and injury issues ====
On 16 August, Raphinha started in Barcelona's La Liga season opener against [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]], scoring their first goal of the league campaign with a seventh minute header assisted by [[Lamine Yamal]], Barcelona went on to win the match 3–0.<ref>{{cite web|last=|first=|title=La Liga Round one - Barcelona vs Mallorca|url=https://www.fotmob.com/en-GB/matches/barcelona-vs-mallorca/2h1xfx#4837114|access-date=2025-12-14|website=Fotmob}}</ref> On 15 September 2025, Raphinha netted a brace in a 6–0 victory against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kepri.antaranews.com/berita/235501/tiga-pemain-cetak-brace-barcelona-kalahkan-valencia-6-0 |title=Tiga pemain cetak brace, Barcelona kalahkan Valencia 6-0 |website=ANTARA News Kepri |date=2025-09-15 |access-date=2026-03-18}}</ref> On 25 September, Raphinha sustained a mid-section tear of the right biceps femoris during a La Liga match against [[Real Oviedo]], forcing him to be substituted in the 65th minute.<ref>{{cite web |last= |first= |title=Raphinha injury news |url= https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4369969/raphinha-injury-news |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=FC Barcelona}}</ref> He was initially expected to be sidelined for three weeks but setbacks meant that he could not return to the field until 22 November, when he came on as a late second half substitute for [[Dani Olmo]] in Barcelona's opening match at the partially renovated [[Camp Nou]] against [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>{{cite web |last= |first= |title=Raphinha, Joan García return to boost Barcelona's Camp Nou return |url=https://www.espn.in/football/story/_/id/47051240/raphinha-joan-garcia-return-boost-barcelona-camp-nou-return |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=ESPN}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last= |first= |title= La Liga Round 13 - Barcelona vs Athletic Club |url=https://www.fotmob.com/en-GB/matches/athletic-club-vs-barcelona/2diy4x |access-date=2025-12-14 |website=Fotmob}}</ref> After returning from injury, Raphinha immediately found his form, providing two assists in his second match back against [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]], which was followed by a goal in his third match back in a 3–1 victory over [[Atlético Madrid]] after Barcelona conceded an early goal from [[Álex Baena]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/soccer/raphinha-sets-up-2-olmo-scores-double-as-barcelona-rebounds-back-from-chelsea-defeat/article_17f711d3-1a47-59e7-8624-54b56ace7c2e.html |title=Raphinha sets up 2, Olmo scores double as Barcelona rebounds back from Chelsea defeat |website=Toronto Star |date=2025-11-29 |access-date=2026-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/dec/02/barcelona-atletico-madrd-la-liga-match-report |title=Raphinha leads comeback for Barcelona in victory against Atlético Madrid |website=The Guardian |date=2025-12-02 |access-date=2026-03-18}}</ref> On 13 December, Raphinha scored both goals in a 2–0 win against [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]], reaching 60 official goals for Barcelona, which equalled Barcelona legend [[Johan Cruyff]]'s tally.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com.br/it/notizie/resumen-del-fc-barcelona-2-0-ca-osasuna-laliga-2526-42093230 |title=Resumen del FC Barcelona 2-0 CA Osasuna - LaLiga 25/26 |website=OneFootball |date=2025-12-13 |access-date=2026-03-18}}</ref> 

On 11 January 2026, he netted a brace and was named man of the match in a 3–2 win over rivals Real Madrid in the [[2026 Supercopa de España final|Supercopa de España final]], finishing the tournament as the top scorer with 4 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rfef.es/en/noticias/Raphinha-named-MVP-of-the-Supercopa-de-Espa%C3%B1a-final-for-the-second-consecutive-year |title=Raphinha named MVP of the Supercopa de España final for the second consecutive year |publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation |date=12 January 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.flashscore.com/news/barcelona-athletic-club-super-cup-report/f9OFBPb4/ |title=Five-star Barcelona demolish Athletic Club to reach Spanish Super Cup final |website=Flashscore.com |date=2026-01-06 |access-date=2026-03-18}}</ref> On 15 March, Raphinha scored his third hat-trick for Barcelona in a 5–2 win against Sevilla.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thesun.my/sports/football/barcelona-thrash-sevilla-5-2-as-raphinha-nets-hat-trick/ |title=Barcelona thrash Sevilla 5-2 as Raphinha nets hat-trick |website=thesun.my |date=2026-03-15 |access-date=2026-03-18 |quote="Playing like this it's hard for teams to beat us. I love this club, and the way to respond from the love I receive from the fans is by scoring goals and kissing the badge."}}</ref> Later that month, he suffered another hamstring injury in an international friendly against [[France national football team|France]], with both the [[Brazilian Football Confederation]] and Barcelona's medical staff predicting that recovery would take approximately five weeks, forcing him to miss crucial Champions League quarter-final matches against Atlético Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4477499/raphinha-injury-news/featured |title=Raphinha injury news |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=27 March 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Menzies |first=John |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2026/03/27/raphinha-ruled-out-champions-league-quarter-final |title=Raphinha ruled out of Champions League quarter-final tie as Barcelona confirm injury news |publisher=Football Espana |date=27 March 2026 }}</ref> Hansi Flick revealed that Raphinha was "very down" and "devastated" after the injury, prompting the club to grant him time off in Brazil with his family to clear his mind before beginning rehabilitation in Barcelona.<ref>{{cite web |last=Marsden |first=Sam |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48385051/barcelona-coach-hansi-flick-urges-marcus-rashford-step-raphinha-injury |title=Barcelona coach Flick urges Rashford to step up after Raphinha injury |publisher=ESPN |date=3 April 2026 }}</ref> On 10 May, he made his return from injury replacing [[Marcus Rashford]] in the 64th minute, as Barcelona won 2–0 over rivals Real Madrid in El Clásico, securing his club's 29th La Liga title, and his third league title with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7260652/2026/05/10/barcelona-real-madrid-clasico-rashford-result-analysis/ |title=Barcelona 2 Real Madrid 0: Hansi Flick's side wrap up La Liga title in El Clasico |publisher=The New York Times |date=10 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Brazil vs Serbia WC2022 Raphinha and Pavlovic (cropped).jpg|thumb|Raphinha (right) with [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] playing against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]
Prior to [[UEFA Euro 2020]], the [[Italian Football Federation]] attempted to call up Raphinha for the [[Italy national football team|Italian national team]], for whom Raphinha was eligible due to his father's heritage. Raphinha has stated that he was close to representing Italy, but did not receive an [[Italian passport]] in time to represent them at the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|date=5 May 2025|title=Italy attempted to convince Barcelona star to play for national team under Mancini|url=https://football-italia.net/italy-attempted-to-steal-barcelona-star/|access-date=5 May 2025|website=Football Italia}}</ref>

In August 2021, Raphinha was selected to represent [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] for the team's [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] qualifiers against [[Chile national football team|Chile]], [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] and [[Peru national football team|Peru]].<ref name="Raphinha Called Up to Brazil's National Squad">{{cite web|date=13 August 2021|title=Raphinha Called Up to Brazil's National Squad|url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/28509/raphinha-called-up-to-brazil-s-national-squad|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210813162311/https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/28509/raphinha-called-up-to-brazil-s-national-squad|url-status=dead|archive-date=13 August 2021|access-date=2 September 2021|website=Leeds United}}</ref> On 7 October, Raphinha made his full debut for the national side, coming on as a substitute at half time in a 3–1 comeback win against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]].<ref>{{Cite web|agency=Reuters|date=8 October 2021|title=Brazil rally to beat Venezuela in qualifier as Raphinha enjoys dream debut|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/oct/08/brazil-venezuela-world-cup-qualifier-raphinha|access-date=15 October 2021|website=The Guardian}}</ref> He assisted two goals and won a penalty in 45 minutes on the pitch, receiving praise from sports pundits and fans.<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 October 2021|title=Raphinha, la nueva joya de Brasil, fue dirigida por Deco y encantó al Loco Bielsa en la Premier League|url=https://www.espn.com.ec/futbol/mundial/nota/_/id/9355119/brasil-raphinha-nueva-joya-dirigida-deco-encanto-loco-bielsa-premier-league|access-date=15 October 2021|website=ESPN.com.co|language=es}}</ref> On 15 October, he scored his first two international goals in a qualifying match against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 October 2021|title=Brazil 4–1 Uruguay: Raphinha scores twice as home side cruise to World Cup qualifying victory|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/world-cup-qualification-conmebol/2022/brazil-4-1-uruguay-raphinha-scores-twice-as-home-side-cruise-to-world-cup-qualifying-victory_sto8585883/story.shtml|access-date=15 October 2021|website=Eurosport}}</ref>

On 7 November 2022, Raphinha was named in the squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] by manager [[Tite (football manager)|Tite]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=7 November 2022 |title=Seleção Brasileira está convocada para a Copa do Mundo FIFA Qatar 2022 |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/selecao-brasileira-esta-convocada-para-a-copa-do-mundo-fifa-qatar-2022|publisher=Brazilian Football Federation|access-date=7 November 2022|language=pt|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231207032652/https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/selecao-brasileira-esta-convocada-para-a-copa-do-mundo-fifa-qatar-2022|archive-date=7 December 2023}}</ref> Brazil reached the quarter-finals of the tournament, where they were eliminated by [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] on 9 December, following a 4–2 penalty shoot-out loss after a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2022/dec/09/croatia-v-brazil-world-cup-2022-quarter-final-live-score-update |title=World Cup quarter-final: Croatia 1–1 Brazil (4–2 pens) – as it happened|newspaper=The Guardian|location=London |date=9 December 2022 |access-date=17 December 2022}}</ref>

On 10 May, Raphinha was called up for Brazil to participate in the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 May 2024 |title=Dorival Júnior anuncia convocados para a Copa América |work=Confederação Brasileira de Futebol |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/dorival-junior-anuncia-jogadores-para-a-disputa-da-copa-america |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240516123444/https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/dorival-junior-anuncia-jogadores-para-a-disputa-da-copa-america |archive-date=16 May 2024 |access-date=10 May 2024 |language=pt-BR}}</ref> He scored his only goal of the tournament against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] in their third group phase game, in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 July 2024 |title=Brasil 1-1 Colombia (2 de Jul., 2024) Resultado Final - ESPN (CO) |url=https://www.espn.com.co/futbol/partido/_/juegoId/690728/colombia-brasil |access-date=20 October 2024 |website=ESPN |language=es}}</ref> Brazil were eliminated from the tournament following a 4–2 penalty shoot-out defeat after a goalless draw against Uruguay in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40486946/copa-america-brazil-boss-slams-ref-booking-vinicius-jr |title=Brazil boss slams 'very strange' Vinícius booking|website=[[ESPN]]|date=3 July 2024 |access-date=10 July 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40524914/vinicius-jr-brazil-copa-america-exit-was-my-fault |title=Vini Jr. on Brazil Copa exit: 'It was my fault'|website=ESPN|date=9 July 2024 |access-date=10 July 2024 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Raphinha is a versatile winger known for his technical ability, agility, pace and defensive work rate. Primarily operating on the [[right winger|right-wing]], he uses his left foot to cut inside, creating goal-scoring opportunities or delivering passes into dangerous areas. His dribbling, characterized by close control, rapid changes of direction, and a blend of speed and creativity, allows him to beat defenders in one-on-one situations. A proficient passer, Raphinha delivers accurate crosses and threads passes into the box, stretching opposition defenses while also operating effectively in tight spaces. Defensively, he plays an important role in counter-pressing, regaining possession by tracking back to support full-backs or disrupting opposition build-up play.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thetitansfa.com/raphinha-player-profile-complete-overview/ |title=Raphinha Player Profile: Complete Overview |website=The Titans FA |date=25 March 2024 |access-date=22 December 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://barcabuzz.com/2022/03/scout-report-is-raphinha-the-right-winger-for-barcelona |title=Scout Report: Is Raphinha the Right Winger for Barcelona? |website=BarcaBuzz |date=21 June 2022 |access-date=22 December 2024 |archive-date=13 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213061249/https://barcabuzz.com/2022/03/scout-report-is-raphinha-the-right-winger-for-barcelona |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://mbpschool.com/en/raphinha-xavi-hernandezs-dream-winger/ |title=Raphinha: Xavi Hernandez's Dream Winger |website=MBP School of Football |date=14 July 2022 |access-date=22 December 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/raphinha-leeds-brazilian-magician/ |title=Raphinha: Leeds' Brazilian Magician |website=Breaking the Lines |date=29 December 2021 |access-date=22 December 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/article/raphinha-2021-22-why-europes-best-are-ready-to-sign-the-brazilian-scout-report |title=Raphinha 2021/22: Why Europe's Best Are Ready to Sign the Brazilian |website=Total Football Analysis |date=5 February 2022|access-date=22 December 2024}}</ref>

At Barcelona under [[Hansi Flick]], Raphinha's tactical role evolved from a traditional winger to a more centrally positioned role as a [[second striker]]. This shift allowed him to exploit spaces between the opposition's defensive and midfield lines, making diagonal runs into the box or drifting inward while other forwards, such as Robert Lewandowski, provided width. By not being confined to the flank, Raphinha stretched the defensive structure, creating additional space and opportunities for himself and his teammates. His quick change of pace and intelligent movement enabled link-up play with players like [[Dani Olmo]], while also supporting attacking moves from deeper positions.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://theconventionalplaymaker.wordpress.com/2024/12/13/8231/ |title= Raphinha is playing more like a second striker, and is making excellent runs|website=The Conventional Playmaker |date=13 December 2024 |access-date=22 December 2024 }}</ref>

==Personal Life==
Raphinha has a long-standing friendship with [[Bruno Fernandes]], starting before they became teammates at [[Sporting CP]].<ref name="12Things"/> He is on record saying Fernandes has been a huge help to him and his footballing career.<ref name="12Things"/> Before joining [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] in the [[Premier League]] for example, Fernandes told him that his style would "fit the league".<ref name="12Things"/>

